# Azure Pricing Intelligence Skill

This skill does three things:
1. Scrapes community channels for trending pricing concerns
2. Pulls official Microsoft wording for Azure cost-saving offers
3. Generates a structured blog outline from any topic prompt

---

## When the user types a topic or asks for a blog outline

→ Go to Phase 3 (Blog Outline Generator) directly.

## When the user asks what's trending or hot right now

→ Run Phase 1 (Scrape) then Phase 2 (Analyze).

---

## Phase 1 — Scrape Community Channels

Read `references/scraping-targets.md` for all URLs and keywords.
Fetch each source, extract: title, URL, date, short excerpt.
Filter by pricing keywords. Rank by recency + engagement.

## Phase 2 — Analyze & Group Topics

Buckets:
- AI/ML Pricing (tokens, Copilot, OpenAI on Azure)
- Compute Cost (VMs, Spot, Reservations)
- Database Cost (SQL MI, Cosmos, PostgreSQL)
- Hybrid/Licensing (Azure Hybrid Benefit, BYOL)
- Budgeting Tools (Calculator, Cost Alerts)
- Savings Plans (1yr vs 3yr, flexibility)

Output as:
### 🔥 Trending Now — [Date]
1. [Topic] — [Source] — [Link] — [Why it matters]

## Phase 3 — Blog Outline Generator

When user provides a topic (e.g. "Azure Savings Plans for VMs"):

1. Search scraping-targets for related community discussions
2. Pull official messaging from `references/official-microsoft-sources.md`
3. Pull offer details from `references/azure-pricing-content.md`
4. Use the template in `references/blog-outline-template.md`

Output a complete blog outline with:
- Suggested title (using official Microsoft language)
- Target audience
- Key pain point from community research
- Section-by-section outline with talking points
- Official Microsoft quotes/stats to include
- Call to action with relevant Azure offer link
